66700.name: 10.6.1 - Proportion of voting rights of developing countries in the Asian Development Bank - SG_INT_VRTADB
66700.datasetName: Proportion of members and voting rights of developing countries in international organizations
66700.s_name: Proportion of members and voting rights of developing countries in international organizations

source.name: Proportion of members and voting rights of developing countries in international organizations
source.additionalInfo:
Definition: 
 
The proportion of members and voting rights of developing countries in international organizations has 
two components, the developing country proportion of voting rights and the developing country 
proportion of membership in international organisations. In some institutions these two components are 
identical. 
 
Comments and limitations: 
 
Cross institutional comparisons needs to pay attention to the different membership of the institutions. 
Voting rights and membership in their institutions are agreed by the Member States themselves. As a 
structural indicator, there will be only small changes over time to reflect agreement on new States joining 
as Members, suspension of voting rights, membership withdrawal and negotiated voting rights changes. 
 

Data Availability 

 
Available for all countries.
